 how ancient biomolecules hold the secrets to how mammoths dealt with the bitter cold, what colors dinosaurs exhibited in mating displays, how ancient viruses evolved to become more dangerous, and much more. Each chapter discusses different types of biomolecules and the insights they provide about the physiology, behavior, and evolution of extinct organisms, many of which existed long before the age of dinosaurs.A marvelous adventure of discovery, Remnants of Ancient Life offers an unparalleled look at an emerging science that is transforming our picture of the remote past. You will never think of fossils in the same way again.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aBiomolecules, Fossil. 0aDNA, FossilxAnalysis. 7aNATURE / Fossils.2bisacsh  aDNA.  aDale Greenwalt The revolution in science.  aDarwin.  aPrinceton University Press.  aRemnants of Ancient Life.  aThe New Science of Old Fossils.  aancient history.  aancient life.  aancient viruses.  abiomolecules.  adinosaurs color.  adinosaurs.  adiscovery.  aemerging science.  aevolution.  afossils.  agenetic material.  ais transforming our understanding of extinct life.  alife on Earth.  aliving organisms.  amammoths.  amolecular traces.  anew dinosaur facts.  anew dinosaur research.  anew discoveries.  anew science.  apigments.  aprehistoric.  aproteins.  arock and minerals.  ascience.  astudy.  atens of millions of years ago.40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780691221151?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780691221151423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780691221151/original  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK